name: George of the Jungle
overview: George of the Jungle is a Canadian television series. It is the remake of the 1967 animated series of the same name, using Adobe Flash animation. It is produced in Canada, and more recently in the USA on Cartoon Network, premiering with the Christmas special. In Latin America, it is airing on Disney Channel. The remake mostly stays true to the original production, with a few key differences existing between the two. One episode of the show typically consists of two 11-minute episodes. This is unlike the original cartoon, which featured other stories such as Tom Slick and Super Chicken. The show's first season ran from June 29, 2007 to January 11, 2008, with a second season to air in 2014.

episodes.name: Beetle Invasion
episodes.overview: George must help stop a beetle infestation that he inadvertently started.

episodes.name: The Naked Ape Man
episodes.overview: George's lack of clothing is called into question.

episodes.name: Aromageddon
episodes.overview: George's body odor after a lengthy time between baths has unforeseen consequences.

episodes.name: Found Temple of Gold
episodes.overview: George is tricked into taking a booby-trapped temple as his new home and desperately tries to undo the trade.

episodes.name: Cone Head
episodes.overview: George must wear a protective cone to keep from scratching an infected itch.

episodes.name: Cousin Larry of the Jungle
episodes.overview: George's arrogant cousin Larry comes for a visit and problems quickly arise.

episodes.name: License to Swing
episodes.overview: Ursula's new vine-swinging system is way too complicated, landing George in Ape's remedial safety class. While there, he falls in with the "bad kids".

episodes.name: My Own Private Hero
episodes.overview: It is Danger Season, when George's pledge to aid all jungle creatures is put to the test. When Big Mitch, a sneaky marmoset, tries to make George his personal danger servant, George's friends attempt to fill in for George and end up in danger themselves.

episodes.name: Lucky Pants
episodes.overview: A pair of underpants is seen as a good luck charm by George and the others. As a result, they each try to claim ownership of them.

episodes.name: Ape Ruth
episodes.overview: George and Ape square off in a series of competitive contests.

episodes.name: Don't Thank Me
episodes.overview: George, Ursula and Magnolia go out of their way to thank Ape for everything (which started when Ape saved George, Ursula and a snake from being eaten by a man-eating plant) to the point where Ape tries to hide from them.

episodes.name: For the Love of Sloth
episodes.overview: George is obsessed with a sloth becoming his friend.

episodes.name: Bathroom of the Apes
episodes.overview: A legend about a curse placed on an outhouse by an ape king may come true.

episodes.name: Beauty vs. Beasts
episodes.overview: George and his friends become obsessed with personal appearance and this is taken advantage of by a pair of scheming peacocks.

episodes.name: Star Power
episodes.overview: George's jungle friends find that their wishes made when they see shooting stars are coming true.

episodes.name: L'il Orphan Anteater
episodes.overview: George cares for a young anteater that he believes is orphaned, but Shep is jealous.

episodes.name: The Vegemaster
episodes.overview: George and his friends, facing a food shortage, travel to meet with a man who calls himself the Vegemaster.

episodes.name: Eagle Tick
episodes.overview: George gains the ability to fly after being bitten by an unusual bug.

episodes.name: The Snoring
episodes.overview: George finds himself helpless to stop Ape's loud snoring at night.

episodes.name: George's Day Off
episodes.overview: At his friends' insistence, George takes a vacation away from the jungle. However, his friends quickly discover that George's duties are very difficult to fill in for.

episodes.name: Frankengeorge
episodes.overview: A zombie curse threatens George and his friends. Everyone in the jungle is turned into zombies hungry for peanuts. Will Ursula escape from such a horrible nightmare?

episodes.name: Afraid of Nothing
episodes.overview: George becomes paranoid after a scary campfire tale and turns his tree house into a fortress.

episodes.name: Brother George
episodes.overview: George is tutored by several different gurus and finds he is supposed to be on three different sides for an upcoming battle.

episodes.name: Ape Mitzvah
episodes.overview: While Ape goes through an annual rite of passage mandated by the Greater Ape Council, George tries to figure out what species he descended from.

episodes.name: Rebel Without a Claw
episodes.overview: George and his friends try to teach the jungle animals to get along, but the natural order gets upset as a result.

episodes.name: Stripy Pony
episodes.overview: Magnolia is determined to have a pony just like the one in her book.

episodes.name: Rainy Season
episodes.overview: George tries to bring an end to a prolonged rainy spell, but the young rain spirit George talks with has other ideas.

episodes.name: Love in the Air
episodes.overview: The Tookie-Tookie Bird is in love with another bird and George cannot understand why such an emotion is so important.

episodes.name: George Skips Breakfast
episodes.overview: George's preparing breakfast for his friends is interrupted by a play being conducted in the area.

episodes.name: Muscle Mania
episodes.overview: Magnolia desires to become stronger, but after bathing in a muscle mutation agent, she transforms into a much larger brute.

episodes.name: Selfish Shellfish
episodes.overview: George finds a seashell on the ground and starts listening to the hermit crab inside constantly. Before long, he is ignoring his friends and treating them badly at the behest of the crab.

episodes.name: Volcano Pageant
episodes.overview: To cheer up a volcano that is supposedly bored, George and his friends put on a show to make it happy.

episodes.name: George Lays an Egg
episodes.overview: George finds a bird's egg with no sign of its mother and decides to care for it until it hatches.

episodes.name: Ape Goes Ape
episodes.overview: Big Mitch's persistent playing of the bongos causes Ape to dance constantly and George resolves to solve the problem.

episodes.name: Mantler, the Man with Antlers
episodes.overview: George enters into a contest in a comic book with hopes of meeting his favorite superhero Mantler personally, but things do not turn out as planned.

episodes.name: Mount Georgemore
episodes.overview: George is stunned to see caricatures of himself carved into a nearby mountain by some of the jungle animals, but finds that it is not a popular thing with many of his friends.

episodes.name: George's Birthday Present
episodes.overview: George's friends learn that George has never celebrated his birthday and set out to get him the ultimate birthday gift.

episodes.name: Witching Stick
episodes.overview: George endeavours to replace the Witch Doctor's stick that he accidentally broke.

episodes.name: Trouble with Bananaquats
episodes.overview: The appearance of bananaquats, which grow once every five years, and the effect they have on Ape has George and Magnolia fearing that bad times lay ahead.

episodes.name: Spoiled King
episodes.overview: George and his friends deal with the antics of a spoiled movie star couple.

episodes.name: Extreme Lamebrains
episodes.overview: Two visitors who record and participate in extremely dangerous stunts visit the jungle. Before long, they have George and Ape doing stunts as well, though all four ultimately are in extreme danger as a result.

episodes.name: Still Got It
episodes.overview: Two legendary pranksters from the past make life difficult for George and the jungle animals.

episodes.name: A Boy and His Elephant
episodes.overview: George decides Shep needs to be trained to make him more obedient to George's requests.

episodes.name: George's Security Stone
episodes.overview: George loses his security stone and searches the jungle to find it and regain his lost confidence.

episodes.name: Jungle Bells
episodes.overview: Ursula, recalling memories of Christmas past, is determined to celebrate Christmas in the jungle, though George and the others are not quite as enthusiastic.

episodes.name: The Goat of Christmas Presents
episodes.overview: On the day after Christmas, everybody (except Ursula) decides to have Christmas again and again.

episodes.name: Second Banana
episodes.overview: Ape tries to be a hero just like his friend George.

episodes.name: One with Nature
episodes.overview: George sets out to meditate and change his grumpy outlook.

episodes.name: Escape from Madmun Island (1)
episodes.overview: George and his friends seek to rescue people trapped on an island populated by mysterious animals and a person who is secretly watching their every move and try to save themselves from the robotic menaces and traps set by the ruler of Madmun Island.

episodes.name: As Strong As He Can Tree
The George Who Would Be King
